I didn't know OSX had a built in wifi signal strength detector....

if you run this script in your shell:
```
while true; do /System/Library/PrivateFrameworks/Apple80211.framework/Resources/airport -I | grep agrCtlRSSI; sleep 0.2; done
```
it'll continuously print the signal strength of the wifi you're connected to
you can symlink it for convenience since the binary path is annoyingly obscure
